The first offensive took place in Yorsala forest where the military said it killed 24 armed men during several hours of fierce fighting in which one soldier died. Eight other suspected militants were killed in Bourzanga, where large quantities of arms and ammunition were seized, the army said. Islamist violence in on the increase in the West African nation. These two military offensives come less than a month since nearly 40 employees of a Canadian mining company were killed in an ambush. Hundreds of people have died and nearly half a million have fled their homes since the unrest began in 2015. --BBC--